{:proof/problem-id "apm-t94J07", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (explicitly references the manifolds \\(X,Y\\), the closed form \\(\\omega\\), and the smoothly homotopic maps \\(f,g\\)) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the formal target assumes only compactness/boundary conditions, closedness of \\(\\omega\\), and the existence of a smooth homotopy) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (the EDN statement by itself encodes the exact equality that must be proved) · notes: helper lemma isolates the Stokes-on-the-cylinder step that bridges the interior integral to the boundary terms.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Use Stokes' theorem on the homotopy cylinder to show that homotopic pullbacks of a closed form have equal integrals.\"\n :terms [{:name \"closed form\"\n          :meaning \"A differential form ω with dω = 0.\"\n          :needed-because \"It makes the Stokes integral over the cylinder vanish (the exterior derivative of the pulled-back form is zero).\"}\n         {:name \"homotopy cylinder\"\n          :meaning \"The manifold X × [0,1] with boundary components X × {0}, X × {1}.\"\n          :needed-because \"The maps f and g appear as the restrictions of a smooth homotopy at the two boundary faces.\"}\n         {:name \"Stokes' theorem\"\n          :meaning \"For a compact manifold with boundary M and a form η, ∫_{∂M} η = ∫_{M} dη.\"\n          :needed-because \"Applying it to the pullback of ω along the homotopy converts the vanishing interior integral into the equality of the two boundary integrals.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"Stokes' theorem on cylinders\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Stage 1 proof uses the trivial homotopy cylinder argument\"\n             :why-this-now \"Pulling ω back along the homotopy H:X×I→Y and applying Stokes immediately relates the two boundary integrals.\"\n             :lean-target \"homotopy_invariance_closed_form_integral\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Stokes' theorem and basic homotopy/pullback APIs exist in mathlib's manifold library, but wrapping them for forms is unfinished.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"Smoothly homotopic maps from a compact boundaryless manifold X to Y pull back any closed form ω to cohomologous forms with identical integrals.\"\n             :formal-name \"homotopy_invariance_closed_form_integral\"\n             :formal-target \"Given compact, boundaryless manifold X, compact manifold Y, a closed form ω on Y, and smoothly homotopic smooth maps f,g : X → Y, one has ∫_X f^*ω = ∫_X g^*ω.\"\n             :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                            :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                            :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                            :notes \"This is the top-level reader-facing statement to be mirrored formally.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"homotopy_invariance_closed_form_integral\"\n              :formal-statement \"For compact manifold-without-boundary X and compact manifold Y, if ω is closed and f,g : X → Y are smoothly homotopic, then the integrals of their pullbacks of ω coincide.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Stage 1 paragraph asserting the equality of the two integrals\"\n              :role :main-theorem}\n             {:formal-name \"stokes_on_homotopy_cylinder\"\n              :formal-statement \"Applying Stokes' theorem to the pullback of ω along the smooth homotopy H : X×[0,1] → Y yields the integral identity on the boundary faces.\"\n              :informal-clause \"Stage 1 sentence invoking Stokes' theorem\"\n              :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n**Why it’s hard / key insight.** The equality links *global* integrals of top-degree forms, not pointwise data, so naïve arguments that compare \\(f^*\\omega\\) and \\(g^*\\omega\\) pointwise go nowhere. The right picture is the homotopy cylinder \\(X\\times[0,1]\\): pull back the closed form along the smooth homotopy \\(H\\) between \\(f\\) and \\(g\\), notice that \\(d(H^*\\omega)=0\\), and apply Stokes’ theorem. Because the boundary of \\(X\\times[0,1]\\) is \\(X\\times\\{1\\}\\cup (-X\\times\\{0\\})\\), the boundary integral is \\(\\int_X g^*\\omega - \\int_X f^*\\omega\\), so the interior integral’s vanishing forces the desired equality.\n\n**Artifacts updated.**\n- `/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/execute.md` now contains the full Stage 1 proof, the Stage 2 dependency graph (Stokes on the cylinder, pullback commuting with \\(d\\), orientation bookkeeping), the Stage 3 status, and the Stage 4 reflection.\n- `proof-plan.edn` already listed the goal/terms/strategy, and its stage-status remains `{... :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}`.\n- `formal-alignment.edn` ties the main informal claim to the Lean target plus the helper lemma “Stokes on the homotopy cylinder.”\n- `changelog.edn` logs the workspace initialization, the Stage 1–2 completion, and a Stage 3 attempt noting the formal blocker (lack of differential-form integration + Stokes in Mathlib).\n\n**Lean status / blocker.** When I opened `/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250/Main.lean`, it became clear that Mathlib currently has no API for integrating top-degree differential forms over compact manifolds-with-boundary, nor a packaged Stokes’ theorem in that generality. Without those primitives (and a way to encode smooth homotopies as maps \\(X\\times I\\to Y\\)), the intended theorem can’t even be *stated* formally, let alone proved. Consequently `lake build ...` still fails because the required theory is missing rather than because of `sorry`s—the Stage 3 section documents this precise gap. Once Mathlib grows that infrastructure, the Lean proof will mirror Stage 1: pull back \\(\\omega\\) along \\(H\\), apply Stokes on \\(X\\times I\\), and read off the two boundary faces.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :proved, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250", :frame/id "apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T02:46:39.273276Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.T94J07.Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250", :proof/problem-id "t94J07", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/t94J07/apm-v2-t94J07-1775011599250/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250/Scratch.lean"}}, :proof/artifacts ["/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250/Main.lean" "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/T94J07/Apm_v2_t94J07_1775011599250/Scratch.lean"], :proof/elapsed-ms 77782}